message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper involves the use of deep learning for segmentation of head and neck anatomy for radiotherapy. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning algorithms for medical image analysis falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also involves the use of medical imaging data and techniques, which makes it relevant to the Medical Imaging (cs.MED) category. Finally, the use of neural networks for segmentation makes it relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NEURON) category.
